y signals at the first mismatch time, I need to store the signals (`in`, `pedge_ref`, `pedge_dut`) when `stats1.errors == 1` and `stats1.errors_pedge == 1`.\\n\\n**3. Implementation Details & Syntax Advice:**\\n*   **Displaying Signals:** A custom task or logic block will be needed to handle the formatted printing (HEX + BIN). Using `$display` with format specifiers (`%h` for hex, `%b` for binary) is key.\\n*   **State Saving:** I will introduce variables to store the signal values corresponding to the first error times.\\n*   **Logic Check:** The original error check `pedge_ref !== ( pedge_ref ^ pedge_dut ^ pedge_ref )` simplifies to `pedge_ref !== pedge_dut`. I will keep the original logic structure but ensure the display logic is robust.\\n\\n**Refinement on Displaying First Mismatch:**\\nThe requirement is: "    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n